Cook - When I make a wrong assumption, I have no problems apologizing. If I was wrong, I am sorry. To answer your question again regarding Spatz, I have a shitload of mailings from him, most I have not read for various reasons. Even though I told him to stop his mailings, I still recieve his stuff.<br><br>
I am curious as to why you have not read threads and posts previous to your first post.<br><br>
Blame? I have never intended to blame you or any else on this site. I never had any problems with your posts when you write on the serious side or with levity. The problem that I continuously see is that the few constant posters on this site devise the plans of ignoring Spatz or the anon's, but come out swinging at first glimpse of the individual. Check to see how many of these there are since you first came aboard. As for the absence of those who wrote in the past, they left when POV first announced the possibility of shuting the site down. Had absolutely nothing to do with you or the others. However, there have been posts of which I found distressing when credentials are questioned, etc.. One example that I might share with you and the others is when someone referred to ClassLass as &quot;...buying leather and chains!&quot; insinuating that she is into S&amp;M or a dyke. If I am wrong here, again, I apologize. But I don't believe so. <br><br>
The problem that I see is that whatever good is posted, the garbage with the anons detract from it.<br><br>
If I seem to be beating around the bush, I don't see it. I do, however, have a real blind spot with regards to my writing. I'll try seriously harder. Your war record and beliefs do not bother me, as a matter of fact, I have enjoyed reading your personal/war writings. There are things on which I would disagree, but I doubt that these would keep us from having a serious and respectable conversation.<br><br>
As far as my health goes, today I am feeling good. Even during my bad days, I have no problems reading the posts, but writing must wait. That is why I did not respond to your, or the others post on site one. I appreciate your concern, but I will try to let one know when I can or cannot respond. That is the only reason why I mention my health problems. Nothing worse than being ignore. I don't want any to think I am ignoring them if I don't respond in a timely manner. You, nor any other are responsible for my health. You cause me no discomfort.<br><br>
I look foward to those posts that we discussed earlier, if that is still possible.<br><br>

